						               													<description>Cubeo is a fast-paced abstract dice game for two players, where no die is rolled.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Although this game is referred to as a board game, no board is needed--a flat surface suffices--and a set of twelve 6-sided dice in two colors, six for each player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The main objective of both players is to put dice on the surface, creating a single 2D formation from them, and either block the opponent from performing any valid action, or be the first player to merge two dice with a total value of more than 6.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the beginning, both players put one die on the playing surface, each facing one dot up, with both dice touching along a side, creating the starting formation. Then during each turn, a player can perform one of the following actions:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1. Add a die to the dice formation touching a friendly die - the newly added die cannot touch any of the opponents' dice.&amp;#10;2. Move a die around the perimeter of the existing formation - the die's value determines the number of steps, and may reverse direction while moving.&amp;#10;3. Merge two friendly dice, provided the player has at least 3 dice in the structure - add the value of adjacent dice, and replace one of the dice indicating the total.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is further required that the dice formation stays connected at all times.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a player merges two dice that add up to a value larger than 6, they win.&amp;#10;Alternatively, if a player can't perform any action, they lose.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
